<section xml:id="sec-types-of-variability">
  <title>Types of Variability</title>
  
  <introduction>
    <p>
      This section explores different sources and types of variability in data, which is fundamental to statistical understanding.
    </p>
  </introduction>

  <objectives>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>Understand different sources of variability</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>Distinguish between natural and systematic variation</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>Recognise the implications of variability for analysis</p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </objectives>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-sources-of-variability">
    <title>Sources of Variability</title>
    <p>
      Variability can come from many sources: natural variation in the phenomenon being studied, measurement error, sampling variation, and more.
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-within-and-between-variation">
    <title>Within and Between Variation</title>
    <p>
      Understanding the difference between variation within groups and variation between groups is crucial for many statistical analyses.
    </p>
  </subsection>

</section>
